                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 7.177,
                                "byte_start": 104755,
                                "byte_stop": 133490,
                                "text": "Justice Ginsburg has our opinion this morning in case 07-371, Taylor versus Sturgell."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 7.177,
                        "stop": 202.162,
                        "byte_start": 133490,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15084,
                            "name": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/ruth_bader_ginsburg",
                            "last_name": "Ginsburg",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2728,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 744958800,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "Bill Clinton",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2728"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32681,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 45030,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/ruth_bader_ginsburg_1_0.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 8135,
                            "identifier": "ruth_bader_ginsburg"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 7.177,
                                "stop": 20.861,
                                "byte_start": 133490,
                                "byte_stop": 188242,
                                "text": "A basic tenet of our system of justice is that anyone who states a claim on which relief can be granted is entitled to his or her own day in court."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 20.861,
                                "stop": 29.069,
                                "byte_start": 188242,
                                "byte_stop": 221052,
                                "text": "Therefore, a judgment in a lawsuit generally does not bind the person without a party to the suit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 29.069,
                                "stop": 38.692,
                                "byte_start": 221052,
                                "byte_stop": 259609,
                                "text": "The question presented in this case, is there a virtual representation exception to this general rule."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 38.692,
                                "stop": 49.771,
                                "byte_start": 259609,
                                "byte_stop": 303913,
                                "text": "Petitioner Brent Taylor filed suit under the freedom of Information Act, seeking certain documents from the Federal Aviation Administration."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 49.771,
                                "stop": 59.156,
                                "byte_start": 303913,
                                "byte_stop": 341424,
                                "text": "Greg Herrick(ph) Taylor\u0027s friend had previously brought an unsuccessful suit seeking the same records."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 59.156,
                                "stop": 73.124,
                                "byte_start": 341424,
                                "byte_stop": 397326,
                                "text": "The two men have no formal legal relationship and there was no evidence that Taylor controlled finance, participated in or even knew about Herrick\u0027s earlier suit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 73.124,
                                "stop": 83.642,
                                "byte_start": 397326,
                                "byte_stop": 439331,
                                "text": "Nonetheless, the Court of Appeals for the D.C. Circuit found that Taylor\u0027s suit was precluded by the judgment against Herrick."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 83.642,
                                "stop": 91.11,
                                "byte_start": 439331,
                                "byte_stop": 469215,
                                "text": "In the Court of Appeals\u0027 view, Herrick had virtually represented Taylor in the prior adjudications."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 91.11,
                                "stop": 106.907,
                                "byte_start": 469215,
                                "byte_stop": 532432,
                                "text": "Under the multifactor test announced by the D.C. Circuit, Herrick qualified as Taylor\u0027s virtual representative because Herrick\u0027s incentive to litigate was at least as strong as Taylor\u0027s."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 106.907,
                                "stop": 115.602,
                                "byte_start": 532432,
                                "byte_stop": 567227,
                                "text": "The two men sought release of the same documents were close associates and hired the same lawyer."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 115.602,
                                "stop": 121.098,
                                "byte_start": 567227,
                                "byte_stop": 589170,
                                "text": "We disapproved the doctrine of preclusion by a virtual representation."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 121.098,
                                "stop": 125.373,
                                "byte_start": 589170,
                                "byte_stop": 606306,
                                "text": "And therefore, vacate the D.C. Circuit\u0027s judgment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 125.373,
                                "stop": 133.465,
                                "byte_start": 606306,
                                "byte_stop": 638698,
                                "text": "As our decision is confirmed, there are several exceptions to the rule against non-party preclusion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 133.465,
                                "stop": 145.751,
                                "byte_start": 638698,
                                "byte_stop": 687808,
                                "text": "But the doctrine of virtual representation adopted by the D.C. Circuit is broader and cloudier than any of the exceptions we have approved."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 145.751,
                                "stop": 159.112,
                                "byte_start": 687808,
                                "byte_stop": 741307,
                                "text": "Our opinion explains why we find the doctrine an unwarranted departure from the general rule that every person is entitled to his or her own day in court."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 159.112,
                                "stop": 168.584,
                                "byte_start": 741307,
                                "byte_stop": 779132,
                                "text": "It was a result reached by the D.C. Circuit nevertheless justifiable under one of the established grounds for nonparty preclusion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 168.584,
                                "stop": 176.383,
                                "byte_start": 779132,
                                "byte_stop": 810375,
                                "text": "Most of those grounds have no application here, but one might cover this case."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 176.383,
                                "stop": 189.466,
                                "byte_start": 810375,
                                "byte_stop": 862724,
                                "text": "Preclusion would be appropriate if Taylor, in pursuing his own suit, is acting not independently, but as Herrick\u0027s agent."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 189.466,
                                "stop": 199.137,
                                "byte_start": 862724,
                                "byte_stop": 901385,
                                "text": "We remand to give the courts below an opportunity to address that yet unresolved issue."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 199.137,
                                "stop": 202.162,
                                "byte_start": 901385,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The Court\u0027s opinion is unanimous."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
